《劝导》本是英国广播公司独家制作，预算75万英镑<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|100}}，制片商后提议与美国波士顿WGBH[[公共廣播|公共电视台]]合作<ref name="Eaton-2013">{{cite book | first = Rebecca | last = Eaton | title = Making Masterpiece: 25 Years Behind the Scenes at Sherlock, Downton Abbey, Prime Suspect, Cranford, Upstairs Downstairs, and Other Great Shows | publisher = Viking | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-0-670-01535-1 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=1uXaphUUpTAC&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210622233102/https://books.google.com/books?id=1uXaphUUpTAC | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-08-01 | archive-date = 2021-06-22}}</ref>，双方过往合作项目包括美国选集电视剧《[[杰作剧场_(电视剧)|杰作剧场]]》、电视剧《傲慢与偏见》等文学改编作品<ref name="Cardwell-2014" />{{rp|89}}。《杰作剧场》执行制片人[[丽贝卡·伊顿|丽贝卡·伊顿]]同意与英国广播公司合作，这一定程度上是因为《劝导》 是她眼中奥斯汀最好的作品<ref name="Eaton-2013" />。剧组预算随之增长<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|100}}。伊顿认为本片堪称电视项目小额投资典范之作<ref>{{Cite news | url = http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-17788229.html | title = PBS' 'Masterpiece Theatre' turns 25 and changes its name | work = [[奈特·里德報業|Knight Ridder]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160530123427/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-17788229.html | date = 1996-01-11 | access-date = 2016-05-30 | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2016-05-30 }}{{subscription needed}}</ref>，但她事后表示如果本片由两小时电影改为六集迷你剧效果会更好<ref name="Eaton-2013" />。法国麦勒西姆制片也投身本片制作，换取节目在法国的电视播映权<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|100}}，影片拍摄预算至此升至一百万英镑<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|100}}。《杰作剧场》主要赞助商[[美孚石油|美孚石油]]也参与本片投资<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|5}}<ref name="Eaton-2013" />。

电影投资商众多，剧组需听取各方意见。麦勒西姆制片对片中部分内容不满，例如该司认为发生在莱姆的剧情“太无聊”，要求全部剪掉<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|102}}。波士顿WGBH向英国广播公司提供详细笔录，内容后纳入剧本<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|102}}，其中一项调整涉及结局。安妮与温特沃斯最终走到一起的高潮戏拍有两版，主要差异为是否接吻。<ref name="guardian1">{{cite news | last = Banks-Smith | first = Nancy | title = Powers of persuasion | work = [[衛報|The Guardian]] | date = 1995-04-17 | page = 8}}</ref>迪尔的剧本完全忠实原著：安妮与温特沃斯在巴斯街头相聚，两人亲切交谈并牵手。伊顿认为要是等待两小时后两人连个嘴都不亲，观众“会难受、烦闷得要发疯”，“吻能提供情感宣泄”，<ref name="guardian1" />波士顿WGBH也认为增加吻戏能让更多受众满意<ref name="Higson-2011" />{{rp|140}}。米歇尔同意妥协并拍摄英国和美国两版，美国版两人亲吻<ref name="Eaton-2013" /><ref>{{cite news | access-date = 2021-08-01 | archive-date = 2020-12-19 | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/the-fine-art-of-persuasion-1616778.html | last = Pearson | first = Allison | title = The fine art of 'Persuasion' | work = The Independent | date = 1995-04-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201219193922/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/the-fine-art-of-persuasion-1616778.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。本片国际版海报采用美版结局画面，男女主角紧紧拥抱<ref name="Eaton-2013" />。部分奥斯汀作品爱好者对美版吻戏不满，鲁特对此表示：“经过长时间的悬念，临近结局你已急不可耐地想看到安妮与温特沃斯上校走到一起，急不可耐！电影毕竟是视觉传媒，或许不用看到他们上床，但亲吻应该不过分”<ref name="BostonGlobe1997" />。

与20世纪70到80年代的名著改编作品相比，英国广播公司90年代的同类作品预算显著上涨，《劝导》因此受益，剧组得以在莱姆里杰斯、巴斯、[[東南英格蘭|東南英格蘭]]乡村实地取景<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|165}}。莱姆、巴斯都是奥斯汀原著涉及的重要地点<ref>{{cite book | first = Valerie Grosvenor | last = Myer | title = Jane Austen: Obstinate Heart | publisher = Arcade Publishing | year = 1997 | isbn = 978-1-61145-813-8 | archive-date = 2021-06-22 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=Aw_ybAobhjMC&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210622233024/https://books.google.com/books?id=Aw_ybAobhjMC | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-08-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | archive-date = 2021-03-08 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/726000/Baths-rich-heritage.html | title = Bath's rich heritage | work = [[每日电讯报|The Daily Telegraph]] | first = Helene | last = Feger | date = 2005-04-23 | access-date = 2021-08-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308150054/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/726000/Baths-rich-heritage.html }}</ref>。迪尔希望片头能在与时代相符的[[英國皇家海軍|英國皇家海軍]]舰艇取景，但剧组只能借到[[第一代纳尔逊子爵霍雷肖·纳尔逊|纳尔逊]]的[[勝利號戰艦|勝利號戰艦]]。船停在[[旱塢|旱塢]]，属朴茨茅斯地方博物馆，演职人员需赶在战列舰不向公众开放的短暂时间拍摄。<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|102}}<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|165}}片尾男女主角看向大海的镜头取自1984年历史题材电影《[[叛舰喋血记_(1984年电影)|叛舰喋血记]]》<ref name="Giddings-Selby-2001" />{{rp|102}}<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|165}}。电影预算不高，片头克罗夫特上将乘舰艇在海上航行的镜头同样取自《叛舰喋血记》<ref>{{cite news | last = Wilmington | first = Michael | title = Adaptation of Austen's 'Persuasion' entertains seamlessly | work = [[芝加哥論壇報|Chicago Tribune]] | date = 1996-10-27 | url = https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-1995-10-27-9510270118-story.html | access-date = 2021-02-25 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210225070934/https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-1995-10-27-9510270118-story.html | archive-date = 2021-02-25 }}</ref>。

== 主题与分析 ==

=== 与原著的差异 ===
迪尔因“保留原著大部分复杂情节和大量人物”赢得赞誉<ref name="screenonline" />，但文学学者也指出电影与原著差异甚大。莎拉·莫里森发现片中安妮表达想法的部分台词绝不可能在小说出现，例如安妮探望贫穷老友史密斯夫人，为此错过体面亲戚举办的聚会，她坚定维护自身决定，但原著“非常清楚地表明，安妮决不可能站在完全平等的立场与父亲争论”。<ref name="Morrison-1999">{{cite journal | last = Morrison | first = Sarah R. | url = http://www.jasna.org/persuasions/on-line/opno3/morrison.html | title = Emma Minus Its Narrator: Decorum and Class Consciousness in Film Versions of the Novel | journal = Persuasions: The Jane Austen Journal On-Line | year = 1999 | volume = Occasional Papers | number = 3 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210415050515/http://www.jasna.org/persuasions/on-line/opno3/morrison.html | archive-date = 2021-04-15}}</ref>片中安妮的部分举动也为原著所无，如温特沃斯听到他人贬损海军的话后心里难受，决定离开音乐会现场，安妮匆忙前去请他留下。莫里森认为这些差异主要是因为小说改编成电影本来就很难，特别是在电影不像小说那样提供第三方讲述人物心理活动的情况下。<ref name="Morrison-1999" />

奥斯汀笔下人物性格微妙，本片对人物情感和部分桥段夸张处理。安妮在小说前段的聚会上像往常一样提议弹钢琴，演奏时眼中蓄满泪水，但又“非常高兴演奏”而且“没人发现”。片中这场戏增加温特沃斯马上起身给安妮让座，随即与马斯格罗夫家族姐妹花共舞的情节，安妮与其他人的区别显得更大。<ref>{{cite journal | last = Stovel | first = Nora Foster | url = http://www.jasna.org/persuasions/printed/number28/stovel.pdf | title = From Page to Screen: Dancing to the Altar in Recent Film Adaptations of Jane Austen's Novels | journal = Persuasions: The Jane Austen Journal | page = 188 | year = 2006 | volume = 28 | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2021-03-08 | format = PDF | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308161655/http://www.jasna.org/persuasions/printed/number28/stovel.pdf | access-date = 2021-08-01 }}</ref>大卫·莫纳汉声称，原著对社会变革看法“比较激进”，例如职业阶层崛起，挑战[[地主阶级|地主阶级]]的新秩序。莫纳汉认为迪尔和米歇尔认同如此立场，并以视觉和动作手段强调。但片中男女主角“全心全意”相爱“严重背离”原著，是迪尔和马歇尔着眼“未来”、照顾20世纪观众情感的举措。<ref>{{cite book | first = David | last = Monaghan | editor1-first = David | editor1-last = Monaghan | editor2-first = Ariane | editor2-last = Hudelet | editor3-first = John | editor3-last = Wiltshire | title = The Cinematic Jane Austen: Essays on the Filmic Sensibility of the Novels | publisher = McFarland | year = 2009 | chapter = 'A Cheerful Confidence in Futurity': The Movement Motif in Austen's Novel and Dear/Michell's Film Adaptation of Persuasion | page = 129 | isbn = 978-0-7864-3506-7 | access-date = 2021-08-01 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=0EPYqh8C2VgC&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210622233102/https://books.google.com/books?id=0EPYqh8C2VgC | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2021-06-22}}</ref>

[[苏·帕里尔|苏·帕里尔]]认为电影预算远比以往充足，演职人员得以实地取景拍摄大部分内容，充分利用实景传达象征意义、营造情绪<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|165}}。例如小说里安妮的心情受天气影响特别大<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|165–66}}。电影片头确立历史背景、埃利奥特家族面临的财务困境<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|166–167}}。雷切尔·布朗斯坦指出，影片开头就有水兵出场，导演此举旨在安抚原著面临的常见批评：没有涉及拿破仑战争<ref>{{cite book | page = 18 | dead-url = no | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=nqf_Wj2Wwx4C&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | last = Brownstein | first = Rachel M. | editor1-first = Linda | editor1-last = Troost | editor2-first = Sayre N | editor2-last = Greenfield | title = Jane Austen in Hollywood | publisher = University Press of Kentucky | year = 2001 | chapter = Out of the Drawing Room, Into the Lawn | isbn = 978-0-8131-9006-8 | access-date = 2021-07-31 | archive-date = 2014-07-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140726162953/http://books.google.com/books?id=nqf_Wj2Wwx4C}}</ref>。皇家海军与埃利奥特家族在片头并列出场，双方截然不同的立场形成反差，皇家海军关注[[拿破仑一世|拿破仑]]战败，埃利奥特家族却在谈论超支带来的些许不便<ref name="Parrill-2002" />{{rp|167}}。

=== 阶级与性别 ===
{{Quote box
 | quote=“故事本质上讲的是旧秩序走向颓废，新精英统治阶层脱颖而出。换言之，它代表十八与十九世纪间的转折点。”
 | source = —编剧尼克·迪尔<ref name="Dear-1996" />
 | width  = 30em
 | align  =right
|bgcolor=#FFFFF0
}}
迪尔的剧本出版成书，序言自称描绘“世界转型”是他改编奥斯汀原著的重要原因<ref name="Dear-1996" />。在他看来，小说“本质上讲的是旧秩序走向颓废，新精英统治阶层脱颖而出”<ref name="Dear-1996" />。罗杰·米歇尔认为电影情节包含“后现代家族原型”：母亲撒手人寰，父亲破产，“旧社会秩序土崩瓦解”<ref name="philly">{{cite news | last = Rickey | first = Carrie | title = Jane Austen, a '90s kind of gal | work = [[費城詢問報|The Philadelphia Inquirer]] | date = 1995-11-13 | archive-date = 2016-03-04 | access-date = 2016-03-04 | url = http://articles.philly.com/1995-11-13/entertainment/25682041_1_jane-austen-janeite-sense-and-sensibility | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304025841/http://articles.philly.com/1995-11-13/entertainment/25682041_1_jane-austen-janeite-sense-and-sensibility | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。鲁特认为安妮是女权思想时代前的女权人士，为人坚强、独立，这样《劝导》虽是古装片，现代观众仍能找到共鸣<ref name="BostonGlobe1997" />。

奥斯汀学者研究本片体现的阶级与社会变革。卡罗尔·多尔指出，20世纪90年代奥斯汀改编作品众多，只有《劝导》“坚持关注阶级议题”，“为英国阶级体系运作提供引人注目的视觉依据”<ref>{{cite book | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=nqf_Wj2Wwx4C&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | last = Dole | first = Carol M. | editor1-first = Linda | editor1-last = Troost | editor2-first = Sayre N | editor2-last = Greenfield | title = Jane Austen in Hollywood | publisher = University Press of Kentucky | year = 2001 | page = 60 | chapter = Austen, Class, and the American Market | isbn = 978-0-8131-9006-8 | access-date = 2021-08-01 | archive-date = 2014-07-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140726162953/http://books.google.com/books?id=nqf_Wj2Wwx4C | dead-url = no}}</ref>。她还称，镜头注意展示仆从的面部，体现他们对各种情节不以为然的看法一定程度上有助于反映上述观念<ref>{{cite journal | last = Dole | first = Carol M. | volume = 27 | issue = 2 | dead-url = no | url = http://www.jasna.org/persuasions/on-line/vol27no2/dole.htm | title = Jane Austen and Mud: ''Pride & Prejudice'' (2005), British Realism, and the Heritage Film | journal = Persuasions: The Jane Austen Journal On-Line | date = Summer 2007 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214020036/http://www.jasna.org/persuasions/on-line/vol27no2/dole.htm | archive-date = 2020-12-14}}</ref>。理查兹同样认为本片在米歇尔执掌下给予下层阶级的镜头更多，片尾黑人仆从暗指阶级与地位更优越的人就是靠“殖民地财富”支撑<ref name="Richards-2003" />{{rp|117}}。安妮-玛丽·肖尔茨指出，本片和[[艾瑪·湯普遜|艾瑪·湯普遜]]编剧的《理智与情感》都强调阶级主题但角度不同。《劝导》描绘整体阶级划分，不像《理智与情感》仅体现工薪阶层对主人翁的影响，本片镜头关注仆人与工人的脸和表情，给予他们个人特征。<ref name="Scholz-2013">{{cite book | first = Anne-Marie | last = Scholz | title = From Fidelity to History: Film Adaptations as Cultural Events in the Twentieth Century | publisher = Berghahn Books | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-0-85745-731-8 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=1VRFAAAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140725210422/http://books.google.com/books?id=1VRFAAAAQBAJ | archive-date = 2014-07-25 | access-date = 2021-08-01}}</ref>{{rp|140}}

米歇尔认为奥斯汀信仰“[[原女性主义|原女性主义]]”，对“世界如何对女人不利洞若观火”<ref name="philly" />，例如书中安妮谈到所有指称女人善变的歌曲和谚语都是男人所作<ref name="philly" />。肖尔茨声称片中安妮的地位趋于边缘化，与仆从联系在一起；安妮乘坐装牲畜的运货马车出行，尖锐反映阶级与性别主题<ref name="Scholz-2013" />{{rp|140}}。朱丽安·皮德克指出，导演“特意突出阶级与性别社会约束主题，举止优雅的社会内部古板无趣，与开阔、诱人的海洋地平线对比显著”<ref name="Pidduck-2000">{{cite book | editor1 = You-Me Park | editor2 = Rajeswari Sunder Rajan | first = Julianne | last = Pidduck | chapter = Of Windows and Country Walks: Frames of Space and Movement in 1990s Austen Adaptations | title = The Postcolonial Jane Austen | publisher = Routledge | year = 2000 | pages = 129 | isbn = 0-415-23290-2 | access-date = 2021-08-01 | archive-date = 2014-07-26 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=x3Kcm-AK_5wC&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140726144554/http://books.google.com/books?id=x3Kcm-AK_5wC | dead-url = no}}</ref>。皮德克以安妮住在巴斯的桥段为例，住宅基本封闭，她从上层窗户凝视下方街道，想找到温特沃斯。对她来说，温特沃斯就像大海一样代表自由和可能<ref name="Pidduck-2000" />。

